commit.message:
Use prepared process handling functions instead of own codes.

* qmtp.el (qmtp-send-package, qmtp-send-buffer): Use
process-live-p.

* smtp.el (smtp-connection-opened, smtp-open-connection): Use
process-live-p.
(smtp-primitive-starttls): Use process-type.

Avoid using string-make-unibyte

It is obsolete function since 26.1.

* tests/test-hmac-md5.el (test-hmac-md5-3, test-hmac-md5-4)
(test-hmac-md5-7, test-hmac-md5-8): As above.

* tests/test-hmac-sha1.el (test-hmac-sha1-3, test-hmac-sha1-4)
(test-hmac-sha1-7, test-hmac-sha1-8): As above.

Don't use multibyte string in test for MD5, SHA1

* tests/test-hmac-md5.el (test-hmac-md5-3, test-hmac-md5-4)
(test-hmac-md5-7, test-hmac-md5-8): As above.

* tests/test-hmac-sha1.el (test-hmac-sha1-3, test-hmac-sha1-4)
(test-hmac-sha1-7, test-hmac-sha1-8): As above.

Remove test for SASL-NTLM

It seems that sasl-ntlm-response() in sasl-ntlm.el doesn't return
stable result. And the file has been removed from FLIM-LB.

* tests/test-sasl.el (test-sasl-ntlm-imap): Removed.

Fix error when loaded without byte-compilation

* mel-q-ccl.el (eof-block-branches, eof-block-reg): Define initial
value.

Run test at run-time, not at macro expansion time

* lunit.el (lunit-assert): As above.
* mel-q-ccl.el: Suppress byte-compiler's warning.

Don't inhibit EOL conversion for oauth2.el.

oauth2.el internally calls url package, which loads saved cookie
file.  The file has file variables and saved as DOS EOL on
Windows.  When EOL conversion is inhibited, loading such file
fails.  As workaround, explicitly enable EOL conversion in calling
oauth2 functions explicitly

* sasl-xoauth2.el (sasl-xoauth2-refresh-access)
(sasl-xoauth2-response): As above.

Use `ash' instead of `lsh'

* mel-q-ccl.el (mel-ccl-high-table, mel-ccl-decode-q)
(mel-ccl-decode-quoted-printable-generic): As above.

* sasl-scram.el (sasl-scram-md5-make-security-info): Likewise.

* sasl.el (sasl-unique-id-function): Likewise.

Fix CCL lexical analyzer fails to parse quoted-string

* mime-parse.el (mime-default-ccl-lexical-analyzer): Fix failing
to parse quoted-string.

* std11.el (std11-default-ccl-lexical-analyzer): Likewise.

Add redirect URI for Gmail

Gmail blocks new clients which use out-of-band (OOB).

* sasl-xoauth2.el (sasl-xoauth2-host-url-table): Add redirect URI
for Gmail.

Update docstring syntax

"'" in docstring has become special character since emacs 25.
Non-special "'" should be escaped.  And, some '(' characters are
escaped with single "\" to avoid mis syntax highlighting.  But the
problem looks to be fixed already.  So I remove the workaround.

* smtp.el (smtp-open-connection-function): Likewise.

* mime-conf.el (mime-format-mailcap-command): Likewise.

* mime-parse.el (mime-parse-parameters): Likewise.
* README: Update requirements.  Wide int feature is required.

Fold docstring within 80 characters

* sasl-xoauth2.el (sasl-xoauth2-host-url-table)
(sasl-xoauth2-host-user-id-table): Likewise.  Remove example.

Remove XEmacs related stuff.

* Makefile (package, install-package): Removed.

* FLIM-MK (config-flim-package, compile-flim-package)
(install-flim-package): Removed.

New installer option PACKAGE_LISPDIR

Specified directory and subdirectories are added to load-path
while compile and installation process.  Typically used for making
elisp files installed via package system visible from installer.
When variable name is specified, use its value as the root
directory.  Default value is 'package-user-dir'.  To disable the
feature, set value to 'NONE'.

* Makefile (PACKAGE_LISPDIR): New variable.
(elc, check, install): Call emacs with PACKAGE_LISPDIR.

* FLIM-MK (config-flim): Set PAKCAGE_LISPDIR from arguments.

* FLIM-CFG: Add directory and subdirectories of PAKCAGE_LISPDIR to
load-path.

Fix problem with new timestamp format.

* sasl.el (sasl-unique-id-function): Do not access internals of
timestamp.

Fold docstring within 80 characters

* mel.el (mel-b-builtin-decode-string)
(mel-b-builtin-decode-region): Likewise.

Fold docstring of customizable variable within 80 characters

* mel.el (mel-b-builtin-garbage-strategy): Likewise.

* mime-parse.el (mime-ccl-lexical-analyzer): Likewise.

* std11.el (std11-unfold-strip-leading-tab)
(std11-ccl-lexical-analyzer): Likewise.

Minor refactorings

* mmgeneric.el (mime-visible-field-p): Remove redundant codes.
(mime-insert-header-from-buffer): Reduce buffer switchings.
* sasl-xoauth2.el (sasl-xoauth2-host-url-table): Add examples. (not tested)

Compare field names in a case insensitive manner

Email header fields are always case-insensitive.  This fixes header
matching for the likes of wl-message-ignored-field-list

* mmgeneric.el (mime-visible-field-p): Bind case-fold-search to t.

Fix last change of std11-narrow-to-header.

* std11.el (std11-narrow-to-header): Fix last change which makes
separator included in narrowed region.

Adjust dependencies.

* mel-q.el: Load path-util.el only when needed.
(exec-installed-p): Declare it for byte compiler.

* mel.el (module-installed-p): Declare it for byte compiler.

* mime.el: Require luna.el.

* mmgeneric.el: Require mcharset.el and std11.el.  Load
eword-decode.el always for mime-find-field-decoder-internal.

Fix https://github.com/wanderlust/flim/issues/14

luna-next-methods and luna-current-method-arguments have to be
defined as dynamic variables at also runtime in lexical binding
environment.

* luna.el (luna-next-methods, luna-current-method-arguments):
Define as dynamic variables always.
* eword-decode.el (eword-lexical-analyze): Minor refactorings.
* std11.el (std11-narrow-to-header): Narrow region only when needed.

Update package description file for MELPA.

* flim-pkg.el: Define supported Emacs version.  Add dependency on
oauth2.el.  It is required by sasl-xoauth2.el.

Remove some codes fo old platforms.

* eword-encode.el (ew-find-charset-rule): Removed.  It is for old
platforms.git log

* mel-q.el: Require pces.el normally.

* mel-q-ccl.el (mel-ccl-16-to-256-table, mel-ccl-u-raw)
(mel-ccl-c-raw, mel-ccl-p-raw, mel-ccl-decode-q)
(mel-ccl-encode-quoted-printable-generic)
(mel-ccl-decode-quoted-printable-generic): Remove char-int usage.

* mime-def.el (char-int): Abolished.  If you really need it, use
poe.el in APEL.
(base64-dl-module): vaule is always nil.

* mime-parse.el (mime-decode-parameter-encode-segment): Remove
char-int usage.

* smtp.el (smtp-use-gnutls): Assume gnutls-available-p is always
available.
Merge branch 'conao3-remove-cvs' into flim-1_14-wl
